# Rust Driver Core — safe wrappers for any driver subsystem

config RUST_CORE
	tristate "Rust Driver Core — safe DMA/PCI/devres wrappers"
	depends on RUST
	help
	  Universal Rust safety layer for all driver subsystems.
	  Provides RAII-style DMA mappings, bounds-checked PCI config
	  access, automatic devres cleanup, and safe MMIO operations.
	  Any Linux driver (GPU, storage, net, USB, audio, etc.) can
	  link against this module to eliminate entire classes of
	  memory-safety and resource-leak bugs.

	  When in doubt, say M.

config RUST_CORE_DMA
	bool "Safe DMA mapping wrappers"
	depends on RUST_CORE
	default y
	help
	  RAII DMA mappings that record device, direction, and length
	  so that unmapping is always correct.  Prevents the most
	  common class of DMA bugs.

config RUST_CORE_PCI
	bool "Safe PCI config space access"
	depends on RUST_CORE && PCI
	default y
	help
	  Bounds-checked PCI configuration space access.
	  Eliminates out-of-bounds config space reads/writes.

config RUST_CORE_DEVRES
	bool "Safe devres (device-managed resource) tracking"
	depends on RUST_CORE
	default y
	help
	  Automatic cleanup for driver resources via the kernel's
	  devres framework, with Rust-level type safety.
